createTSVNoLoadSPEF(25.10)                          createTSVNoLoadSPEF(25.10)

Name
       createTSVNoLoadSPEF  - Creates a top-level spef that describes the con-
       nectivity between dies

Syntax
       createTSVNoLoadSPEF

       <fileName>

       Creates a top-level spef that describes the connectivity between  dies.
       The RC is 0 in this SPEF file, but only inter-die connectivity is writ-
       ten.  This spef file, together with the spef for each die, is the input
       of Tempus for static timing analysis.

       This command is used after reading the stacked die  config  file  (XML)
       using  readTSVConfig as the die configuration is required to detect the
       connectivity between dies.

Parameters
       <fileName>
              Specifies the file name.

Examples
              * The following command creates a 0 load top-level spef file:

                createTSVNoLoadSPEF top.spef

Related Information
              * readTSVConfig

